snippet.textDisplay:
Honestly, I think Brave has the right idea. Opt-in ads with rewards. It's the right psychological approach. Take something that's seen as a "punishment" (viewing ads), and make it a reward instead. People who don't think it's worth it don't get penalized (needing to install ad blockers), and people who are okay with ads get rewarded.

The outcome is more or less the same, but everyone is happier.
